@NODE AboutLODGE "About LODGE..."
In 1991 I bought an Amiga 500 after using a ZX Spectrum 128 for 4 years.
Dealing with the Amiga after years of fiddling around with the Spectrum 
seemed to be more difficult than I expected. Luckily I knew someone who 
already owned an Amiga, and he explained the basics to me well enough so
I didn't drop the Amiga. The Amiga owning circle of friends grew and at 
the moment there are five of them.
Since the summer of 1992 we form a software development group. Initially 
we called ourselfs 'TBL' (The Black Lodge), after the evil shadow world 
from David Lynch's 'Twin Peaks' series.
A few weeks ago, after we released our first finished piece of software
called 'The AGA Experience' and received some very nice responses, 
but also a less pleasant message. The Swedish group  'The Black Lotus' 
were (rightfully) objecting to us using the abbreviation 'TBL', because 
they have been using it since 1988 for their group. We're not lame, so 
we immediatly changed the name of our group to LODGE, keeping some of 
the original name intact. Officialy LODGE is an abbreviation of:

     @{b}L@{ub}ast of the @{b}O@{ub}riginal @{b}D@{ub}ivision of @{b}G@{ub}raphical @{b}E@{ub}ntities 

     @{i}Click here @{ui}>>>@{b}@{" Keepers " LINK KeepersLODGE}@{ub}<<<@{i} to learn more about the keepers of LODGE.@{ui}

@ENDNODE

