@NODE List "The LODGE programs..."

        @{fg fill}All these programs are or will be available from Aminet.@{fg text}
	@{u}                                                        @{uu}

@{b}The LODGE AGA Experience Demo@{ub}
A demo everyone with an Amiga 1200 or 4000 should have. It's great! All
those colours make you glad you have an AGA Amiga! Expect new versions
soon!

@{b}Valkyr's Non Productivity Tools@{ub}
This range of nice screen hacks and un-utilities is available from AmiNet.
Check them out, they are quite funny.

@{b}TimeCalc v1.0@{ub}
This program took us almost 3 year to complete. Now it is finally available
on Aminet. It is a very comprehensive clock and calendar program with a
host of unique options. At the moment the source-code is rewritten to make
it function even better than it does already. There are also plans for a
professional version in the pipeline. Keep watching the Net!
@{i}(ETA: Late fall 1995)@{ui}

@{b}StripHTML v1.1@{ub}
StripHTML is available from Aminet. With it you can remove all those 
useless HTML codes, so you can print WWW texts with any old word processor.

@{b}Cartograph@{ub}
Hmmm... This is a bit of a neverending story. When the development of this
program continues at it's current pace, it will be available around the
summer of 2003. (probably) :o(

@{b}Breakin' Briks v1.0@{ub}
Now this is it. It's a great Breakout clone for AGA Amiga's. The version
currently available from Aminet will ASAP be updated with an even better
version. If you liked Megaball, you'll love Breakin' Briks.

@{b}Cyber Cycles@{ub}
This program is not exactly ready to be released. A lot of graphics work 
and fine tuning has to be done. We hope the game will be available before 
the end of 1996. One things for sure: it will be very fun to play! :)

@{b}Very Important Pixels@{ub}
Well, you're looking at it right now... Check it out!

@{b}ChartMaker@{ub}
With this program you can make... charts! (what's in a name?) Details on
this program are very vague, so you'll have to wait until it appears in
the recent list of Aminet, sometime at the end of this century...

@{b}Currently untitled shoot 'm up@{ub}
This one is in a very early stage. It will involve hords of aliens to kill,
multidirectional scrolling, AGA graphics and a great soundtrack. As I said
before: "@{i}Keep your eyes on the Aminet recent list!@{ui}"

@{b}D. Lusion's Module Collection@{ub}
A large collection of Protracker modules made in recent years by the
musical LODGE member D. Lusion. The collection can be found in the MODS
directory of Aminet. 

Of course there are more plans, but they are very very unfinished.
Amongst the future projects is VIPS II, with glorious AGA pictures 
of more (recent) famous people...

