@NODE MakingOfVIPS "The making of VIPS..."

The pictures in this archive were originaly intended to be in a slideshow 
called 'VIPS - Very Important Pixels'. As you will notice they are all in 
320*256*16 format.
This is because when the pictures were digitized in the summer of 1992 I 
had no access to an AGA-Amiga. I'm not even sure if I ever heard of AGA 
back then...
The pictures were grabbed by Andre Haberkorn from a VHS video tape using 
the Rombo VidiAmiga frame grabber. The pictures formed a television advert 
for 'De Krant op Zondag' (Newspaper on Sunday) which doesn't exist anymore.

The musical score was composed and programmed by @{"D. Lusion." LINK DLusion}
He made a special 1995 re-mix of the original 1992 soundtracker module for
this Aminet release.

The ShowVIPS IFF viewer was programmed by @{"Valkyr" LINK Valkyr} and is a (very) sneak 
preview of his upcoming slideshow viewer which at this moment hasn't
got a name... It's still quite buggy, so use at your OWN risk!
Valkyr also solved some big problems concerning the ill behavior of the
AmigaGuide System command. The smart guys and gals amongst you will 
understand what I'm talking about... Again: Use the solution at your
OWN risk.

@{"Go Back" LINK Main}

